      "widgets_values": [
        "ATLAS INPAINT LAYERS — 2.5D clean-plate parallax (partial example: in-repo Atlas nodes only)\n\nSplits the solved photo into two depth bands (background + foreground), derives each band's own relief mesh (AtlasCleanPlateLayer), and layers them as separate ProjectionSources so a dolly/orbit move reveals INPAINTED background instead of black holes — see docs/dev/atlas_inpaint_layers_design.md and CLAUDE.md's 'Inpaint layers' key design rule.\n\nThis graph uses only in-repo Atlas nodes; the external inpaint step (Acly/comfyui-inpaint-nodes) is represented as a placeholder link + note (see the note near the background layer) since those nodes aren't installed in this repo/session and their class_types can't be validated here. Wire in the real inpaint chain per INSTALL.md before expecting a genuinely inpainted reveal.\n\nOnce wired: open the Atlas Viewport below, hit 📽 Project, then dolly/orbit in — the background layer should now show inpainted content, not black, where the foreground uncovers it."
