        "EXTERNAL INPAINT STEP (not included here — needs Acly/comfyui-inpaint-nodes, GPL-3.0):\n\nThe link feeding AtlasCleanPlateLayer (bg)'s plate_image is a PLACEHOLDER — it reuses the original LoadImage output directly, just so this graph stays valid/runnable without the external pack installed.\n\nTo build a real clean plate, replace that link with:\n  AtlasDepthLayerMask.occlusion_mask -> INPAINT_ExpandMask (grow ~16-32) -> INPAINT_InpaintWithModel (image=original LoadImage output, inpaint_model=INPAINT_LoadInpaintModel loading big-lama.pt) -> AtlasCleanPlateLayer (bg).plate_image\n\nSee INSTALL.md's 'Optional Inpaint Integration' section for install steps.\n\nThe foreground layer needs no inpainting at all — it's wired directly to the original photo, since nothing occludes the frontmost layer."
